f diverse populations to their own piece of the suburban American Dream. It follows one community over several decades as it transforms from a sleepy rural town to a global gateway and one of the nation's largest Asian American–majority cities. There, it highlights the passionate efforts of Asian Americans to make Silicon Valley their home by investing in local schools, neighborhoods, and shopping centers. It also provides a textured tale of the tensions that emerge over this suburb's changing environment. With vivid storytelling, Trespassers? uncovers suburbia as an increasingly important place for immigrants and minorities to register their claims for equality and inclusion.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 05. Dez 2022) 0aAsian AmericanszCaliforniazSanta Clara Valley (Santa Clara County). 0aSuburbszCaliforniazSanta Clara Valley (Santa Clara County). 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Discrimination & Race Relations.2bisacsh  aamerican dream.  aasian american studies.  aasian american.  achina.  achinese immigrants.  ademographics.  adiversity.  aeconomy.  aenvironmental.  aequality.  aethnic diversity.  agentrification.  aglobal.  agoogle.  aimmigration.  ainclusion.  aindia.  aindian immigrants.  amigration.  aminority groups.  apopulation growth.  aracial diversity.  aracial identity.  aregional.  asilicon valley.  asouthern california.  asuburban.  ataiwan.  ataiwanese immigrants.  atech economy.  atech industry.  atechnology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z97831106675540 cprintz978052029389240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520967229423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520967229/original  a978-3-11-066755-4  University of California Press Complete eBook-Package 